MAMELODI Suundowns have revealed that the family of defender Motjeka “Ace” Madisha are still awaiting DNA results that will confirm whether or not the person who died in the horror crash in the early hours of Sunday morning, is indeed their son. In a statement by the club, they stated that Madisha's family met with the pathologists on Monday with regard to the identification of their son. "The nature of the horrific car crash that took place on the Zuurfontein Road near Chloorkop requires that all processes be followed by the necessary authorities with relevant expertise to confirm the identity of the driver," read the statement. "The Madisha family requests privacy and the relevant protocols be followed during this difficult period of uncertainty. Mamelodi Sundowns will communicate further details after consultation with the Madisha family once the DNA test results have been released." 